title: 22 build unit tests
body:
Added unit tests for business entities, use cases, and controllers.  Also renamed the business test cases (from SME as part of user story).

I noticed the way these tests were written introduced some duplication of coverage.  This duplication happens because we have unit tests for everything and because UIQuarter is used by BasePeriod, which is in turn used by CalculateBasePeriod (use case) which is used by BasePeriodController.  So the result seems to be that UIQuarter is really covered 4 times, BasePeriod 3 times, CalculateBasePeriod 2 times, and BasePeriodController just the once.  I'm not necessarily saying this is a problem, but something for us to discuss going forward to make sure DWD is happy with the amount of unit testing coverage - not too little and not too much.

title: #73 GetBenefitYear fails due to invariant culture
body:
Do to a lack of understanding of the dotnet environment variables, the container set DOTNET_SYSTEM_GLOBALIZATION_INVARIANT=1 and it should not have. This was not picked up in unit tests as tests are not run with these environment variables set.

I was able to make the unit tests fail be introducing the environment variables.

title: fixes #95 refactor wage api to accept a quarter list
body:
Fixes #98

Following our discussion of LinqKit this morning I found an alternate implementation that appears to be an improvement on LinqKit and adapted it as a new local shared package, DWD.UI.PredicateBuilder.

Following is the query generated for the Linq to Entities query for the in-memory database, where the ultimate SQL is not available. This is an intermediate syntax based on two year-quarter tuples in the query. As you can see, with an arbitrarily large collection of query tuples, this would quickly become unwieldy, but moreover, I don't know of a way to add OR predicates ANDed to another predicate in Linq.

DbSet<ClaimantWage>()
    .Where(p => p.ClaimantId == <>c__DisplayClass8_0.claimantId && False || (int?)p.WageQuarter == (int?)(int)<>c__DisplayClass8_1.quarter.QuarterNumber && (int?)p.WageYear == (int?)(int)<>c__DisplayClass8_1.quarter.Year || (int?)p.WageQuarter == (int?)(int)<>c__DisplayClass8_1.quarter.QuarterNumber && (int?)p.WageYear == (int?)(int)<>c__DisplayClass8_1.quarter.Year)

title: Updating development-guidelines.md to include PATs

Since SSO is needed in DWD, we've added instructions for setting it up.
Credentials aren't prompted for since you need authorization just to see

title: Added GCP Workflow spike yaml for task 76 and 93
body:
This PR includes a single YAML file that contains the source code used for the GCP Workflow spike in the DWD GCP environment.  This workflow / spike are related to the following tasks:

Technical Task #76 - Research Orchestration of current APIS in GCP
Technical Task #93 - Securely calling an on-prem API from GCP

This code includes some commented-out sections that were formerly used to retrieve and process wage data from the lab environment.  I kept them in the code so that I can preserve that code, and will later remove the areas and update the header comments.

The top of the file contains a description of the actions being performed and the configuration settings.

An automated deployment mechanism is not yet set up.  In order to deploy, you must manually edit the workflow and paste in the contents of the yaml file.
